Lettuce, tomato, onion.

01:36.730 --> 01:38.764
Uh, pickles.

01:38.766 --> 01:40.833
And tzatziki sauce.

01:40.835 --> 01:43.535
Oh, and, uh,
a little hot sauce, too.

01:43.537 --> 01:46.205
Hot sauce, okay.

01:50.611 --> 01:52.211
Hi.

01:52.213 --> 01:53.779
Thank you, ma'am.

01:53.781 --> 01:56.682
You're welcome. God bless.

02:07.594 --> 02:08.526
Hi!

02:08.529 --> 02:09.261
Hey, lady.

02:09.263 --> 02:12.764
"O god, why do you
cast us off forever?

02:12.766 --> 02:13.732
Why does your anger smoke

02:13.734 --> 02:16.201
against
the sheep of your pasture?

02:16.203 --> 02:20.205
Remember your congregation,
which you acquired long ago,

02:20.207 --> 02:23.275
which you redeemed to be
the tribe of your heritage."

02:26.714 --> 02:28.647
Can I just...

02:31.484 --> 02:34.319
Sisters of mercy.

02:34.321 --> 02:35.921
Who? Colleen?

02:35.923 --> 02:40.392
No, we don't have
any sisters named that.

02:41.327 --> 02:44.329
No, ma'am, I don't know.

02:44.331 --> 02:46.265
Do you know which order?

02:46.267 --> 02:48.800
Oh, yeah, then I
definitely don't know.

02:48.802 --> 02:52.771
There are so many.
I'm sorry.

02:53.640 --> 02:55.574
Oh, that's okay.

02:55.576 --> 02:59.411
Hope you find her.
God bless.

03:40.920 --> 03:43.956
I think the people understand.

03:43.958 --> 03:47.359
I'm a war president.

03:47.361 --> 03:49.728
I hear the voices,
and I read the front page,

03:49.730 --> 03:53.532
and I know the speculation,
but I'm the decider.

03:53.534 --> 03:55.567
But I'm the decider.

03:55.569 --> 04:01.240
And I ask you whether you
recall the title of that PDB.

04:01.242 --> 04:02.641
I believe the title was

04:02.643 --> 04:08.280
<i>bin laden determined to attack
inside the United States.</i>

04:08.916 --> 04:12.317
You know that, that old
beach boys song <i> Barbara Ann?</i>

04:12.319 --> 04:13.752
We're going to do
what we have to do

04:13.754 --> 04:15.854
to protect
the United States of America.

04:15.856 --> 04:17.456
The message
of these brave men and women

04:17.458 --> 04:22.027
who are serving over there
is "let us win."

04:22.796 --> 04:25.264
And night fell
on a different world,

04:25.266 --> 04:29.001
on a world where freedom itself
is under attack.

04:47.453 --> 04:48.487
Sorry.

04:48.489 --> 04:50.389
You're Debbie's friend.

04:50.391 --> 04:50.822
Yeah.

04:50.824 --> 04:53.425
You're the nun.

04:53.427 --> 04:53.992
Um, yeah...

04:53.994 --> 04:58.730
So, you, like, devoted your life
to Christ and everything?

05:00.901 --> 05:01.500
You did.

05:01.502 --> 05:02.801
I thought the show
was really creative.

05:02.803 --> 05:04.770
Thank you. That's all right.
I don't want to mess with you.

05:04.772 --> 05:07.639
It's just I've never
seen one before.

05:07.641 --> 05:10.042
I've never seen
a real live nun before.

05:10.044 --> 05:11.410
It's okay.

05:11.412 --> 05:11.877
Sorry.

05:11.879 --> 05:14.646
Do you wanna do
some blow with us?

05:14.648 --> 05:17.049
Oh, I can't.

05:17.051 --> 05:17.916
Sorry. Thanks.

05:17.918 --> 05:20.085
I have no idea
how you would get, like,

05:20.087 --> 05:23.755
I don't know, like a record deal
or a record company

05:23.757 --> 05:24.923
or any of that, but...

05:24.925 --> 05:26.758
I just think like,
you're so talented,

05:26.760 --> 05:30.629
and, and if you can,
then, and if you'd like to,

05:30.631 --> 05:31.363
then you should,

05:31.365 --> 05:34.599
you should share
your gift with the world.

05:35.401 --> 05:36.702
I don't know.
I don't know.

05:36.704 --> 05:40.972
Just that's what my parents
always told me.

05:41.774 --> 05:46.478
The next
Manhattan-bound l train

05:46.480 --> 05:51.583
will depart
in approximately 37 minutes.

06:11.872 --> 06:14.439
Sorry.

06:19.012 --> 06:22.581
Do you remember
what I said to you

06:22.583 --> 06:27.152
when you first joined our order,
Joan of arc?

06:27.154 --> 06:28.587
Mm-hmm.

06:28.589 --> 06:30.756
Do you think I was right?

06:32.892 --> 06:35.093
No.

06:35.095 --> 06:36.995
You think I was wrong.

06:40.967 --> 06:42.934
I'm sorry.

06:48.141 --> 06:51.176
You're very close
to your first vows,

06:51.178 --> 06:56.882
and I'm having trouble believing
that you're really devoted...

06:56.884 --> 06:58.583
I am devoted.

06:58.585 --> 07:00.118
Sorry.

07:02.722 --> 07:05.590
I don't want you
to not have fun.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.426
You're young.
You should have fun.

07:07.428 --> 07:09.961
But if this community
isn't offering you

07:09.963 --> 07:12.531
enough fun already...

07:17.904 --> 07:19.905
What's wrong?

07:27.647 --> 07:29.614
Hey.

07:29.616 --> 07:32.083
I like your sunglasses.

07:34.487 --> 07:36.521
Thanks.

08:53.065 --> 08:56.668
You want to borrow my car,
don't you?

08:58.938 --> 09:01.306
For how long?

09:02.608 --> 09:06.545
Um, I don't know.

09:06.547 --> 09:07.546
Three or four days.

09:07.548 --> 09:12.117
You must tell me a number
and stick with it.

09:16.622 --> 09:19.691
It took god six days
to create the universe.

09:19.693 --> 09:23.295
You should be able to get
your act together in five.

09:25.865 --> 09:28.300
Okay.

09:28.302 --> 09:31.069
Okay, five days.

09:33.239 --> 09:35.974
Use the time wisely, sister.

12:58.410 --> 12:59.978
Hello?

13:23.302 --> 13:24.936
Jacob?

13:29.875 --> 13:31.810
Hello?

15:01.967 --> 15:04.903
<i>Starlings are
medium-sized passerines.</i>

15:04.905 --> 15:08.306
<i>The shortest-bodied species
is Kenrick's starling,</i>

15:08.308 --> 15:12.076
<i>but the lightest-weight species
is Abbott's starling</i>

15:20.019 --> 15:21.986
holy cow.

15:23.022 --> 15:24.522
Hi, dad.

15:32.965 --> 15:35.066
You look great.

15:37.303 --> 15:40.204
You smell a little weird.

15:43.475 --> 15:46.945
You smell like always.

15:48.515 --> 15:50.415
Oh, Chiclet!

15:50.417 --> 15:53.051
The more things change, huh?

15:53.053 --> 15:54.218
Hi!

15:54.220 --> 15:54.953
Joani!

15:54.955 --> 15:56.187
I'm getting the bags!

15:56.189 --> 15:58.990
Joani, get in here, now!

16:08.300 --> 16:10.234
Hi, mom.

16:11.103 --> 16:13.471
Oh!

16:13.473 --> 16:17.275
Oh, sweet pea.

16:18.377 --> 16:20.278
Oh, you're home.

16:20.280 --> 16:22.146
Oh, you're home!

16:22.148 --> 16:24.349
Sweet pea!

16:24.351 --> 16:27.285
- Mmm!
- Oh!

16:28.253 --> 16:31.723
Look what the cat dragged in.

16:31.725 --> 16:33.024
Hey, Colleen.

16:33.026 --> 16:35.059
Hey, Tricia.

16:39.198 --> 16:42.467
Did you, did you get my emails?

16:42.469 --> 16:44.035
Uh, yeah.

16:44.037 --> 16:44.502
Yeah?

16:44.504 --> 16:48.406
Um, I'm on, um, medicine now.

16:48.408 --> 16:50.341
Did you know that?

16:51.310 --> 16:52.210
That's good, mom.

16:52.212 --> 16:57.115
Yeah.
I'm so happy you're home.

16:57.117 --> 17:00.051
Did you see your brother?
Did you say hi?

17:00.053 --> 17:01.352
I didn't know
he was home until...

17:01.354 --> 17:03.321
Oh, I'm going to go,
I'm going to go get him.

17:03.323 --> 17:04.422
No, you don't have to do that.

17:04.424 --> 17:06.156
Yes, I'm going to go get him.

17:06.159 --> 17:07.425
Mom!

17:08.160 --> 17:10.127
Mom!

17:11.563 --> 17:15.165
Hey, want to see something cool?

17:16.335 --> 17:18.636
Hey, come on.

17:21.406 --> 17:23.074
<i>Are you looking for a band</i>

17:23.076 --> 17:25.443
<i>for your wedding, birthday,
or corporate event?</i>

17:25.444 --> 17:28.780
<i>Pro-star entertainment
has a wide variety of musicians</i>

17:28.782 --> 17:30.148
<i>for your every need.</i>

17:30.150 --> 17:32.617
<i>From smooth jazz
to classic rock,</i>

17:32.619 --> 17:34.819
<i>country, calypso, and beyond.</i>

17:34.821 --> 17:36.587
<i>Our professional attitude...</i>

17:36.589 --> 17:40.124
Oh, wow.

17:40.126 --> 17:41.225
What?

17:41.227 --> 17:42.226
Pretty neat, right?

17:42.228 --> 17:43.694
<i>Give pro-star entertainment</i>

17:43.696 --> 17:46.097
<i>a call today at pro-star.</i>

17:46.099 --> 17:48.466
That was really something.

17:53.473 --> 17:56.774
I hope you're still hungry
for dinner.

18:00.180 --> 18:02.346
<i>The latest polls
show a majority of Americans</i>

18:02.348 --> 18:04.115
<i>think Democratic senator
Joe Biden</i>

18:04.117 --> 18:07.785
<i>won last night's
vice presidential debate.</i>

18:17.596 --> 18:21.599
So, you really stuck
with that vegetarian thing, huh?

18:21.601 --> 18:22.233
Yep.

18:22.235 --> 18:25.203
When you were little,
all you wanted were nuggets.

18:25.205 --> 18:26.537
Chicken nuggets.

18:26.539 --> 18:31.809
"Papa" nuggets, remember?
Big ol' papa nugget.

18:33.279 --> 18:37.482
Oh, man, this
really hits the spot.

18:39.518 --> 18:41.486
Is anybody going to get that?

18:45.491 --> 18:51.195
They wanna put your brother
on CNN.

19:34.274 --> 19:36.174
Colleen?

19:37.209 --> 19:38.276
Colleen.

19:38.278 --> 19:39.477
Yeah?

19:39.479 --> 19:41.245
Your mom and I
are dropping Tricia off

19:41.247 --> 19:42.513
and heading into the office.

19:42.515 --> 19:45.883
Are you going to be okay here
by yourself?

19:45.885 --> 19:47.818
Uh, yeah.

19:47.820 --> 19:53.925
Hey, give your brother
some space, okay?

19:53.927 --> 19:56.194
Okay.

19:56.929 --> 19:58.729
<i>We love you, mama and papa!</i>

19:58.731 --> 20:01.432
<i>We think that you're
the bee's knees!</i>

20:01.434 --> 20:03.267
<i>We're happy you got married</i>

20:03.269 --> 20:06.537
<i>and gave birth
to Colleen and me.</i>

20:07.406 --> 20:10.541
<i>You help us with our homework.
You take us to the zoo.</i>

20:10.543 --> 20:12.743
<i>And that's why
on this special day,</i>

20:12.745 --> 20:15.379
<i>we're saying
happy anniversary to you!</i>

20:15.381 --> 20:16.881
<i>We know you'll never leave us,</i>

20:16.883 --> 20:18.616
<i>and we swear
on the stars above...</i>

20:19.519 --> 20:20.952
<i>To be good for you forever</i>

20:20.954 --> 20:22.286
<i>and give you all our love!</i>

20:22.288 --> 20:24.455
Welcome wagon!

20:24.457 --> 20:27.658
<i>Happy anniversary!</i>

20:29.428 --> 20:32.230
Uh, hey, there.
Is Jacob home?

20:32.232 --> 20:38.869
Uh, I don't think he's taking
any visitors right now.

20:38.871 --> 20:42.840
Wait a second.
Shoot. Colleen?

20:43.709 --> 20:44.375
Yeah.

20:44.377 --> 20:46.877
Look at you, girl, all grown up!

20:46.879 --> 20:48.913
Like a, like a librarian
or something.

20:48.915 --> 20:51.415
I barely recognized you
without all the, uh, the,

20:51.417 --> 20:53.251
you know, the Marilyn Manson
stuff on your face.

20:53.253 --> 20:59.590
It's like the ugly duckling has
turned into a beautiful swan.

21:01.928 --> 21:06.731
So, uh, we should come back
a little later, then?

22:12.865 --> 22:14.865
Jacob?

22:14.867 --> 22:17.601
Who is it?

22:17.603 --> 22:20.037
Uh...

22:20.039 --> 22:22.406
It's your sister.

22:33.852 --> 22:35.920
Welcome home.

22:40.025 --> 22:41.625
Thanks.

22:42.728 --> 22:44.862
You look different.

22:53.939 --> 22:56.974
Is it okay to hug you?

22:56.976 --> 22:58.576
Sure.

23:08.553 --> 23:09.854
I'm sorry.

23:09.856 --> 23:13.524
Don't worry about it.

23:13.526 --> 23:15.459
I love you.

23:23.602 --> 23:25.936
Do you wanna hang out?

23:25.938 --> 23:28.172
Not really.

24:09.848 --> 24:10.815
Emily.

24:10.817 --> 24:12.850
Oh, my god. Colleen!

24:12.852 --> 24:16.120
You should tell me
when you're back in town!

24:16.122 --> 24:18.456
Well, it's an unexpected visit.

24:18.458 --> 24:23.027
Oh, my god!
You're, like, a real nun now.

24:23.029 --> 24:24.695
Almost.

24:24.697 --> 24:28.899
Everybody's talking
about your brother.

24:28.901 --> 24:32.036
His whole face, huh?

24:32.038 --> 24:32.870
Mm-hmm.

24:32.872 --> 24:34.171
I'm so sorry.

24:34.173 --> 24:36.807
I had such a crush on him
in high school.

24:36.809 --> 24:40.644
I was at my parents'
vacation house,

24:40.646 --> 24:43.214
but they didn't actually say
I could be there,

24:43.216 --> 24:47.785
so technically I was squatting.

24:49.855 --> 24:51.655
Oh, wow.

24:51.657 --> 24:55.726
Yeah, remember this place?

24:55.728 --> 24:58.195
It looks exactly the same.

25:04.569 --> 25:09.573
I'm gonna go take a shower,
wash off the granola.

25:09.575 --> 25:11.709
Make yourself at home.

25:11.711 --> 25:13.143
Okay.

25:33.032 --> 25:34.265
I came into work,
and he was like,

25:34.267 --> 25:37.535
"you're ugly,
and you have a bad personality,"

25:37.537 --> 25:39.870
and so I hit him in the eyes.

25:39.872 --> 25:44.141
And then he had to get surgery,
but that was his fault because...

25:44.143 --> 25:47.678
Yeah, yeah,
and I had to listen to them

25:47.680 --> 25:48.779
talk about how great they are

25:48.781 --> 25:53.984
and, like, how they're
doing this artist residency

25:53.986 --> 25:56.186
in Barcelona
and all these things.

25:56.188 --> 25:59.924
And that's annoying,
but then I realized...

26:05.964 --> 26:07.631
Wow.

26:09.301 --> 26:12.136
I hope this is okay.

26:12.138 --> 26:14.238
Whatever, dude.

26:17.342 --> 26:20.210
You sure you don't want one?

26:22.714 --> 26:24.248
Is that like a nun thing?

26:24.250 --> 26:28.285
It's still a Colleen thing.

26:28.287 --> 26:30.154
Wow.

26:32.123 --> 26:35.859
Do you still have your v-card?

26:35.861 --> 26:37.995
Lifetime member.

26:38.798 --> 26:42.933
How were we friends
in high school?

26:43.602 --> 26:46.637
No one else liked us.

26:46.639 --> 26:49.673
Oh, yeah.

26:49.675 --> 26:52.643
So, why did you move home?

26:59.885 --> 27:04.021
<i>We are here inside
the Findlay corp chicken farm.</i>

27:04.023 --> 27:10.294
<i>Findlay slaughters thousands
of innocent birds every day.</i>

27:10.296 --> 27:11.962
That's awful.

27:11.964 --> 27:17.768
Yeah, so, I had to get out
of Michigan pretty fast.

27:17.770 --> 27:19.303
Do Rick and Sherry know?

27:19.305 --> 27:22.806
No, they just think
I'm a screw-up.

27:22.808 --> 27:26.310
Whatever, it's fine.
We hardly even talk.

27:31.082 --> 27:33.951
Did you get arrested?

27:34.953 --> 27:36.920
Uh-uh.

27:36.922 --> 27:39.089
Thank god.

27:41.026 --> 27:46.063
You know the government
considers us terrorists?

27:46.065 --> 27:48.065
You know what a terrorist is?

27:48.067 --> 27:51.301
It's somebody who
actually does something.

27:51.303 --> 27:52.302
People want to vote for change,

27:52.304 --> 27:55.806
but they don't actually
want to do the changing.

27:55.808 --> 27:56.974
I worked for Peta.

27:56.976 --> 28:01.278
I went to the marches.
Nothing happened.

28:01.280 --> 28:02.379
When I started doing this stuff,

28:02.381 --> 28:04.214
then I could feel
something happening.

28:04.216 --> 28:08.919
I could feel the difference
we were making.

28:08.921 --> 28:13.357
If that makes me a terrorist,
then whatever.

28:17.128 --> 28:20.764
Some people need to be
terrorized sometimes.

28:20.766 --> 28:22.700
<i>The latest jobs report is in</i>

28:22.702 --> 28:25.969
<i>from the labor department,
and it does not look good.</i>

28:25.971 --> 28:28.072
<i>The figures show
that American companies</i>

28:28.074 --> 28:29.206
<i>are laying off employees</i>

28:29.208 --> 28:31.175
<i>at the fastest rate
in five years,</i>

28:31.177 --> 28:35.379
<i>with over 159,000 jobs lost
since September.</i>

28:37.316 --> 28:40.751
Where you been?
Your father and I made dinner.

28:40.753 --> 28:43.821
We had no idea
you'd be home so late.

28:44.489 --> 28:45.923
I ran into Emily Rhoades.

28:45.925 --> 28:48.092
Oh, well, you could've called.

28:48.094 --> 28:52.062
We had no way
of getting in touch with you.

28:52.197 --> 28:54.932
Uh, you haven't had a way
to get in touch with me

28:54.934 --> 28:56.066
for like three years.

28:56.068 --> 28:59.403
Seriously?

29:03.975 --> 29:05.509
I'm sorry.

29:07.445 --> 29:09.813
I'll call next time.

29:09.815 --> 29:13.150
There's some dessert
in the fridge.

29:39.245 --> 29:42.045
Why is this door locked?

29:42.047 --> 29:43.247
I'm getting dressed!

29:43.249 --> 29:48.018
I don't like locked doors
in my house.

29:48.020 --> 29:52.122
I'm putting my clothes on!

29:52.124 --> 29:53.991
Okay, fine.

30:14.547 --> 30:17.481
Are you okay?

30:17.483 --> 30:18.882
Excuse me?

30:20.052 --> 30:23.320
You seem maybe not okay.

30:24.489 --> 30:27.157
I just didn't want you
to miss breakfast.

30:34.332 --> 30:35.465
Scrapple, kiddo?

30:35.467 --> 30:37.000
No, no!

30:37.002 --> 30:38.235
Oops.

30:38.237 --> 30:38.869
No meat.

30:38.871 --> 30:40.470
Mr. bacon greasy fingers!

30:40.472 --> 30:45.475
It's barely meat!
Just eat around it.

30:46.110 --> 30:50.848
So, I am gonna drop Tricia off
at David's farm.

30:50.850 --> 30:54.918
Do you wanna come say hello?
He'd love to see you.

30:54.920 --> 30:55.986
Terri, too.

30:55.988 --> 30:58.222
I, um, I don't think so.

30:58.224 --> 31:02.459
I, um, was hoping Jacob
and I could...

31:07.165 --> 31:09.566
Okay, yeah, sure,
that'd be fine.

31:11.403 --> 31:13.070
Cool.

31:19.310 --> 31:22.179
Take your pick!
Whatever you want!

31:22.181 --> 31:22.946
Hi, uncle David!

31:22.948 --> 31:28.151
Oh, look at you!
Aw! Scrawny little thing.

31:28.153 --> 31:31.655
Don't they feed you
up in New York?

31:31.657 --> 31:32.656
This place looks great!

31:32.658 --> 31:34.224
- Yeah, you like it?
- Mm-hmm.

31:34.226 --> 31:36.627
Terri always wanted
her own little herb farm,

31:36.629 --> 31:38.929
so she's finally got it.

31:38.931 --> 31:39.463
In the meantime,

31:39.465 --> 31:42.132
I'm the one that has
to take care of this place.

31:42.134 --> 31:45.669
But I did get to name the goats!

31:46.605 --> 31:48.906
Shut up, Blanche!

31:48.908 --> 31:50.374
She's my favorite.

31:50.376 --> 31:52.542
Tricia,
why don't you take Colleen

31:52.544 --> 31:53.944
on a little tour of the farm

31:53.946 --> 31:57.948
because David and I have
some business to discuss.

31:57.950 --> 31:59.917
Five minutes, sweet pea.

31:59.919 --> 32:02.419
Okay. Okay.

32:03.421 --> 32:07.124
I think it's great you and Jacob
are still together.

32:07.126 --> 32:09.059
Uh, thanks.

32:09.061 --> 32:12.229
It's, um...

32:12.231 --> 32:14.464
Yeah.

32:14.466 --> 32:17.067
Don't my parents
drive you crazy?

32:17.069 --> 32:19.670
Oh, they're not that bad.

32:19.672 --> 32:22.372
At least they care.

